ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-1.5"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate text-sm font-base">Synthesized practical framework for building Claude-powered support agent</span><span class="inline-flex transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 -rotate-90"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Synthesized practical framework for building Claude-powered support agent</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Good question. Let me break this down practically, given your specific context.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What "building a customer support agent" actually means here</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">You're not writing software from scratch. You're designing the intelligence layer: what the agent knows, how it responds, what it can and can't do. The technical implementation can be minimal.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The simplest viable version (no coding required)</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Use <strong>Claude.ai Projects</strong>. You can:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Upload your knowledgebase/FAQs as documents</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Write a detailed system prompt that defines the agent's behavior, tone, escalation rules</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Test it against real ticket scenarios</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This is already a functional agent. It's not deployed to customers, but it demonstrates the design thinking.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>A step up: a shareable prototype</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Use <strong>Anthropic's API + a no-code tool</strong> like:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Zapier or Make (Integromat)</strong> to connect Claude to a form or email inbox</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Botpress or Voiceflow</strong> for a proper chat interface on top of Claude</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Both have free tiers and don't require coding knowledge.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What makes it worth showcasing</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The build itself is secondary. What matters is the documentation around it:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">What problem it solves (e.g. reducing Tier 1 ticket volume for Total Battle support)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">What you fed it (knowledgebase scope, ticket categories)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">How you designed escalation logic</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Metrics you'd use to measure success</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That framing is directly relevant to your vendor manager role because it mirrors what you'd evaluate in a BPO or vendor.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Concrete starting point</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Before anything else: do you have access to a sanitized version of your current knowledgebase or FAQ content you could use as training material for the agent? That determines which path is realistic.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
