ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-1.5"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate text-sm font-base">Charted next steps for repository initialization</span><span class="inline-flex transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 -rotate-90"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Charted next steps for repository initialization</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Repository is live. Good start.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Now the real work begins. The repo is currently an empty shell with just the description. You need to fill it with actual content.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Next steps in order:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>1. Write the README first</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Click the pencil icon (edit) on the README.md file. This is your main showcase document. I can write you a proper README template right now based on your actual role and context at Scorewarrior if you want.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>2. Then add these files one by one</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Click "Add file" &gt; "Create new file" for each:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">system-prompt.md</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">knowledge-base/faq-template.md</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">sample-conversations/tier1-example.md</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">evaluation-criteria.md</code></li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The honest bottleneck</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The README and system prompt are where you'll spend most of your time, and they need to reflect genuine thinking about your support operation. Generic content will look hollow to anyone who reads it.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Before I help you write anything, I need to understand your actual context better:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">What are the most common ticket types your agents handle in Total Battle support?</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Do you have escalation tiers defined already?</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">What languages does your team support?</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That information will make the agent design (and therefore the repository) credible rather than generic. Want to start with the README or the system prompt?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
