ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-1.5"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate text-sm font-base">The user prompt is empty, so I cannot determine the primary language. However, based on the thinking block being in English, here is my summary:

Identified profile details and strategized integration approach</span><span class="inline-flex transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 -rotate-90"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">The user prompt is empty, so I cannot determine the primary language. However, based on the thinking block being in English, here is my summary:

Identified profile details and strategized integration approach</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Good. Two things I can see from this:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>1. Update your README first</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">I can see your LinkedIn URL is <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">www.linkedin.com/in/alexandros-alexakis</code>. Go back to GitHub and update the README author section - replace <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">YOUR-LINKEDIN-URL</code> with <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">alexandros-alexakis</code>. Small detail but looks unprofessional if left as a placeholder.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>2. Add the repo to LinkedIn</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Click <strong>"Add section"</strong> &gt; scroll down to <strong>"Featured"</strong> &gt; select <strong>"Links"</strong> &gt; paste your GitHub repo URL.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That puts it front and center on your profile, visible to anyone who visits.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>One observation on your profile while I can see it:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your headline says "Building Scalable Player Care Operations" which is solid. Once the GitHub repo is live and linked, you could update it to something like:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Vendor Manager &amp; L&amp;D Lead @ Scorewarrior | Player Care Operations | AI Agent Design</code></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That signals the new skill without overstating it. You're not an AI engineer but you've demonstrated applied AI thinking in your domain, which is accurate and relevant.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Want to also draft a LinkedIn post announcing the project?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
